---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { sectionUrl } from '../../lib/paths';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
	title="Dinastía — album review · Music blog"
	description="Album review: Dinastía by Peso Pluma and Tito Doble P. — Spencerprod."
>
	<link
		slot="head-extra"
		rel="stylesheet"
		href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;0,800;1,400;1,600;1,700&family=Source+Serif+4:opsz,wght@8..60,300;8..60,400&display=swap"
	/>

	<p class="section-eyebrow">Music blog</p>
	<h1 class="mb-page-title">Music blog</h1>
	<p class="section-lede">Hot takes. Correct takes. Mine.</p>

	<article class="mb-review" aria-label="Album review: Dinastía">
		<p class="mb-meta">April 1, 2026 · Album review</p>

		<header class="mb-hero">
			<p class="mb-kicker">Album review</p>
			<h2 class="mb-album-title">Dinastía</h2>
			<p class="mb-artists">Peso Pluma &amp; Tito Doble P</p>
			<div class="mb-rating-row">
				<span class="mb-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars">★★★★★</span>
				<span class="mb-essential-label">Essential listening</span>
			</div>
		</header>

		<div class="mb-prose">
			<p>
				There are albums that entertain, and then there are albums that define a moment. Dinastía falls firmly into the
				latter category. From the very first notes, Peso Pluma makes his intentions clear: this is a statement record, one
				that sets a tone and refuses to let go. The intro does exactly what a great opener should — it signals that
				something special is about to unfold.
			</p>
			<p>
				Spanning a rich standard tracklist and a generous deluxe edition, Dinastía is a showcase of the range and
				confidence that has made Peso Pluma one of the most compelling voices in regional Mexican music. Not every track
				reaches the same heights, but the peaks are extraordinary.
			</p>
		</div>

		<h3 class="mb-section-head">The standard cuts</h3>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--standout">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Dopamina</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--standout">Standout</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				A crowd favorite in every sense of the phrase, &ldquo;Dopamina&rdquo; is the kind of track that earns its reputation
				night after night on stage — and fittingly serves as the album&apos;s concert closer. It hits with the immediacy of
				a song that was designed to be heard at full volume with a crowd around you.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--deep">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Ni Pedo</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--deep">Deep cut</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				A solid song in its own right, &ldquo;Ni Pedo&rdquo; is the type of track you return to occasionally rather than
				compulsively. It suffers less from any quality deficit and more from the company it keeps — surrounded by some of the
				strongest material on the project, it can feel underserved by the spotlight.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--deep">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Putielegante</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--deep">Deep cut</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				Much the same can be said for &ldquo;Putielegante&rdquo; — a track that, on a lesser album, would stand out with
				ease. Here it gets swallowed by the sheer ambition of what surrounds it. The record is simply too good for certain
				songs to breathe as freely as they might deserve.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--standout">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">7-3</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--standout">Standout</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				From the moment those opening horns arrive, &ldquo;7-3&rdquo; announces itself as something special. The energy
				built in the introduction never dissipates — it carries through the entire runtime with a momentum that feels both
				deliberate and effortless. One of the album&apos;s most viscerally satisfying cuts.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--favorite">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Billete</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--favorite">Personal favorite</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				Criminally underappreciated by the general conversation around this album, &ldquo;Billete&rdquo; is, in this
				listener&apos;s estimation, an absolute hidden gem. It carries an unmistakable flex energy — the kind of track that
				sounds deceptively cool at home but transforms into something otherworldly in a live setting. The crowd energy it
				generates is exactly what this type of song was built for.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--standout">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Daño</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--standout">Standout</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				A genuine emotional centerpiece. Peso&apos;s vocal performance on &ldquo;Daño&rdquo; is among the most affecting on
				the entire record — there is a tenderness in the delivery that reaches places most tracks in this genre do not even
				attempt. Beautiful, unhurried, and deeply moving.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--muted">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Trucha</h4>
			</div>
			<p>
				Fast, aggressive, and relentless — &ldquo;Trucha&rdquo; pulls no punches. The collaboration between Tito Doble P and
				Peso is immediate and hooky; you are locked in from the first bar. It&apos;s the kind of track that demands your
				full attention and rewards it.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--muted">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Morras II</h4>
			</div>
			<p>
				As a sequel to &ldquo;Las Morras&rdquo; from <em class="mb-em">Genesis</em> — an album that deserves its own conversation as
				perhaps the definitive record of its genre — this track carries significant expectations. On first listen it
				reads as understated, and repeated plays soften but do not entirely dispel that impression. It is far from bad, but
				it is not the kind of song you reach for instinctively.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--standout">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Mezcal</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--standout">Standout</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				The opening vocals on &ldquo;Mezcal&rdquo; are an immediate signal that something different is at work here. It
				offers a genuine breath of fresh air — distinct enough to feel like a detour, cohesive enough to feel essential. The
				thematic continuity with the rest of the album is never broken; it simply offers a new angle on familiar territory.
			</p>
		</section>

		<blockquote class="mb-pullquote">
			<p>When Malibu ended, there was only one instinct: play it again.</p>
		</blockquote>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--favorite">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Malibu</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--favorite">Personal favorite</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				Perhaps the single greatest surprise on the album. &ldquo;Malibu&rdquo; catches you from the very first moment and
				refuses to release its grip. It holds a rare quality — the ability to feel both complete and insufficient at the
				same time, leaving you wanting to start it again the second it ends. A legitimate top-tier moment on an album full
				of them.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--muted">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">20&apos;s</h4>
			</div>
			<p>
				Smooth, groovy, and entirely in its lane. &ldquo;20&apos;s&rdquo; is the kind of track that settles into your body
				before your brain has a chance to process it — head-nodding, unhurried energy that rewards an attentive listen in a
				quiet room as much as it does anything else.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--favorite">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Viejo Lobo</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--favorite">Personal favorite</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				Like &ldquo;Malibu&rdquo; before it, &ldquo;Viejo Lobo&rdquo; announces its distinctiveness immediately — there is
				something in its texture that sounds unlike anything else on the record. The collaboration between Peso and Tito here
				reaches a genuine artistic peak. This is the definition of a masterpiece cut: the kind of song that reminds you why
				you listen to music in the first place.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--muted">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Tú Con Él</h4>
			</div>
			<p>
				One of the album&apos;s most emotionally resonant moments, &ldquo;Tú Con Él&rdquo; is the track that tends to find
				its audience among those who feel things deeply. On the initial pass through the album it stood as an immediate
				favorite — and while repeated listens have reshuffled the rankings, placing it just behind &ldquo;Billete,&rdquo;
				&ldquo;Malibu,&rdquo; &ldquo;7-3,&rdquo; &ldquo;Dopamina,&rdquo; &ldquo;Daño,&rdquo; and &ldquo;Viejo Lobo,&rdquo;
				it remains a beautifully crafted piece of music that earns its place.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--muted">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Bckpckbyz</h4>
			</div>
			<p>
				An anthem for the grind. &ldquo;Bckpckbyz&rdquo; speaks directly to anyone who has come up from nothing and is still
				in the process of building — it captures that specific feeling of shared ambition, of looking at the people beside you
				and understanding the road still ahead. This one belongs to those moments with your people.
			</p>
		</section>

		<div class="mb-rule" role="separator">
			<span class="mb-rule-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
			<span class="mb-rule-label">Deluxe edition</span>
			<span class="mb-rule-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
		</div>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--deluxe">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Chiclona</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--deluxe">Deluxe · Best of the bonus</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				The clear standout of the deluxe additions and, frankly, one of the best songs on the entire expanded project.
				&ldquo;Chiclona&rdquo; sits comfortably in the same conversation as &ldquo;Dopamina&rdquo; and &ldquo;Billete&rdquo;
				— an argument for its inclusion on the standard tracklist is not a difficult one to make.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--deluxe">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">London</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--deluxe">Deluxe</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				A strong second showing from the bonus material, &ldquo;London&rdquo; holds its own with confidence. It fits the
				album&apos;s sensibility naturally and leaves you glad it made the cut.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--deluxe">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Ganga</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--deluxe">Deluxe</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				Kinetic, breathless, and impossible to sit still through — &ldquo;Ganga&rdquo; is one of those songs that hijacks
				your body the moment it starts. Whether you are in a car, a room, or anywhere in between, it moves you. A worthy
				addition to an already loaded runtime.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mb-track mb-track--deluxe">
			<div class="mb-track-head">
				<h4 class="mb-track-name">Marianita</h4>
				<span class="mb-pill mb-pill--deluxe">Deluxe</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				Sharing clear DNA with &ldquo;Ganga,&rdquo; &ldquo;Marianita&rdquo; arrives as an elevated variation on a theme
				rather than a wholly distinct statement. It does what it sets out to do — but with &ldquo;Ganga&rdquo; already
				present on the same project, it inevitably reads as the slightly lesser iteration of the same energy. Good, but
				outpaced by its sibling.
			</p>
		</section>

		<div class="mb-verdict">
			<p class="mb-verdict-label">Final verdict</p>
			<p class="mb-verdict-text">
				Dinastía is the work of an artist firing on all cylinders. Tracks like &ldquo;Malibu,&rdquo; &ldquo;Viejo
				Lobo,&rdquo; &ldquo;7-3,&rdquo; &ldquo;Billete,&rdquo; and &ldquo;Daño&rdquo; are the kinds of songs that remind you
				what great music feels like — immediate, visceral, and emotionally true. Not every moment lands at the same altitude,
				but that is the nature of an ambitious full-length record. What Peso Pluma delivers here is something that cements
				his place at the top of the conversation. Essential listening.
			</p>
		</div>

		<p class="mb-back">
			<a href={sectionUrl(base, 'music')}>← My Music (releases)</a>
		</p>
	</article>
</Layout>

<style>
	/* Editorial review: Playfair Display + Source Serif 4; scoped to this page via .mb-review + .mb-page-title */
	.mb-page-title {
		font-family: var(--font-display);
	}

	.mb-review {
		--mr-playfair: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
		--mr-serif: 'Source Serif 4', 'Source Serif Pro', Georgia, serif;
		--mr-text: var(--text);
		--mr-muted: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 48%, var(--bg));
		--mr-faint: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 22%, var(--bg));
		--mr-hairline: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 32%, transparent);
		--mr-border-muted: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 18%, var(--bg));
		--mr-border-strong: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 72%, var(--bg));
		--mr-favorite: #9b7fa6;
		--mr-favorite-dim: color-mix(in srgb, #9b7fa6 18%, var(--bg));
		--mr-amber: #c17f3a;
		--mr-amber-surface: color-mix(in srgb, #c17f3a 14%, var(--bg));
		--mr-pill-standout-bg: var(--surface);
		--mr-pill-standout-border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 14%, var(--bg));
		--mr-verdict-fill: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 92%, var(--bg));

		max-width: 38rem;
		margin-top: 1.25rem;
		padding-bottom: 3rem;
		background: transparent;
	}

	@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
		.mb-review {
			--mr-verdict-fill: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 6%, var(--bg));
			--mr-pill-standout-bg: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 8%, var(--bg));
			--mr-pill-standout-border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 20%, var(--bg));
		}
	}

	.mb-meta {
		font-family: var(--mr-serif);
		font-weight: 300;
		font-size: 0.8125rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--mr-muted);
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
	}

	.mb-hero {
		border-top: 2.5px solid var(--mr-text);
		padding-top: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.mb-kicker {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 0.18em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--mr-muted);
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
	}

	.mb-album-title {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 6vw, 3rem);
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
		color: var(--mr-text);
	}

	.mb-artists {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.2rem);
		font-style: italic;
		font-weight: 400;
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
		color: var(--mr-muted);
	}

	.mb-rating-row {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.65rem 1rem;
		padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
		border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--mr-hairline);
		margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
	}

	.mb-stars {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		line-height: 1;
		color: var(--mr-text);
	}

	.mb-essential-label {
		font-family: var(--mr-serif);
		font-size: 0.6875rem;
		font-weight: 300;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--mr-muted);
	}

	.mb-prose p,
	.mb-track p,
	.mb-verdict-text {
		font-family: var(--mr-serif);
		font-weight: 300;
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
		line-height: 1.72;
		margin: 0 0 1.15rem;
		color: var(--mr-text);
	}

	.mb-em {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-style: italic;
		font-weight: 400;
	}

	.mb-section-head {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-size: 1.35rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin: 2.5rem 0 1.25rem;
		color: var(--mr-text);
	}

	.mb-track {
		margin-bottom: 1.35rem;
		padding: 1.1rem 1.15rem 1.1rem 1.25rem;
		border-left: 2px solid var(--mr-border-muted);
		background: transparent;
	}

	.mb-track--muted {
		border-left-color: var(--mr-border-muted);
	}

	.mb-track--standout {
		border-left-color: var(--mr-border-strong);
	}

	.mb-track--deep {
		border-left-color: var(--mr-faint);
	}

	.mb-track--favorite {
		border-left-color: var(--mr-favorite);
	}

	.mb-track--deluxe {
		border-left-color: var(--mr-amber);
	}

	.mb-track-head {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
	}

	.mb-track-name {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--mr-text);
		flex: 1 1 auto;
		min-width: 0;
	}

	.mb-pill {
		font-family: var(--mr-serif);
		font-size: 0.625rem;
		font-weight: 400;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		padding: 0.35rem 0.65rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		flex-shrink: 1;
		min-width: 0;
		max-width: 13rem;
		text-align: center;
		line-height: 1.35;
		hyphens: auto;
	}

	.mb-pill--favorite {
		background: var(--mr-favorite-dim);
		color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--mr-favorite) 55%, var(--text));
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--mr-favorite) 35%, transparent);
	}

	.mb-pill--standout {
		background: var(--mr-pill-standout-bg);
		color: var(--mr-text);
		border: 1px solid var(--mr-pill-standout-border);
	}

	.mb-pill--deep {
		background: transparent;
		color: var(--mr-muted);
		border: 1px solid var(--mr-faint);
		opacity: 0.92;
	}

	.mb-pill--deluxe {
		background: var(--mr-amber-surface);
		color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--mr-amber) 45%, var(--text));
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--mr-amber) 40%, transparent);
	}

	.mb-pullquote {
		margin: 2.5rem 0;
		padding: 1.35rem 1rem;
		text-align: center;
		border-top: 0.5px solid var(--mr-hairline);
		border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--mr-hairline);
		background: transparent;
	}

	.mb-pullquote p {
		font-family: var(--mr-playfair);
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-style: italic;
		font-weight: 400;
		line-height: 1.45;
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--mr-text);
	}

	.mb-rule {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 3rem 0 2rem;
		width: 100%;
	}

	.mb-rule-line {
		flex: 1;
		height: 0.5px;
		background: var(--mr-hairline);
		min-width: 1.5rem;
	}

	.mb-rule-label {
		font-family: var(--mr-serif);
		font-size: 0.6875rem;
		font-weight: 300;
		letter-spacing: 0.2em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--mr-muted);
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.mb-verdict {
		margin-top: 2.75rem;
		padding: 1.35rem 1.5rem 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 0.5px solid var(--mr-hairline);
		background: var(--mr-verdict-fill);
	}

	.mb-verdict-label {
		font-family: var(--mr-serif);
		font-size: 0.6875rem;
		font-weight: 300;
		letter-spacing: 0.2em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--mr-muted);
		margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
	}

	.mb-verdict-text {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.mb-back {
		margin-top: 2.75rem;
		padding-top: 1.5rem;
		border-top: 0.5px solid var(--mr-hairline);
		font-family: var(--mr-serif);
		font-weight: 300;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
	}

	.mb-back a {
		color: var(--text);
		font-weight: 400;
	}
</style>
